  "text": "## Prometheus Metrics Exposition Pattern: Kubernetes vs Grafana\n\n### Overview\n\nBoth Kubernetes and Grafana implement the Prometheus metrics exposition pattern using the prometheus/client_golang library, but they organize their metrics infrastructure differently based on their architectural needs.\n\n### Kubernetes Architecture\n\n**Registry Management (legacyregistry):**\nKubernetes uses a centralized metrics registry pattern in `staging/src/k8s.io/component-base/metrics/legacyregistry/registry.go`. The key components are:\n\n- **defaultRegistry**: A single global `metrics.NewKubeRegistry()` that serves as the central metrics repository\n- **DefaultGatherer**: Exposes the gatherer interface for collecting metrics\n- **Handler() and HandlerWithReset()**: Factory functions that return HTTP handlers instrumented with `promhttp.InstrumentMetricHandler()`\n- **MustRegister**: Global function that registers metrics with the default registry\n\nThe registry automatically includes Go runtime and process metrics via collectors registered in the init() function (line 54-56), and includes Kubernetes-specific prometheus extensions.\n\n**Metrics Routes (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/routes/metrics.go):**\nKubernetes exposes metrics via route installation classes:\n\n- **DefaultMetrics**: Installs `/metrics` endpoint using `legacyregistry.Handler()`\n- **MetricsWithReset**: Installs `/metrics` endpoint with DELETE method support via `legacyregistry.HandlerWithReset()`\n- **register() function**: Explicitly registers multiple metric collectors:\n  - apimetrics.Register()\n  - cachermetrics.Register()\n  - etcd3metrics.Register()\n  - flowcontrolmetrics.Register()\n  - peerproxymetrics.Register()\n  - handlersmetrics.Register()\n\n**Distributed Metric Definition Pattern:**\nKubernetes defines metrics across many modules using a consistent pattern. Example from `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/audit/metrics.go`:\n\n- Metrics are defined as package-level variables (eventCounter, errorCounter, levelCounter, ApiserverAuditDroppedCounter)\n- Each metric uses `metrics.NewCounter()` or `metrics.NewCounterVec()` with metadata (Subsystem, Name, Help, StabilityLevel)\n- Metrics are registered in init() functions via `legacyregistry.MustRegister()`\n- StabilityLevel is enforced for metric governance\n\n**Metrics Provider Pattern:**\nKubernetes uses interface-based metric providers for pluggable metrics. In `staging/src/k8s.io/component-base/metrics/prometheus/workqueue/metrics.go`, the `prometheusMetricsProvider` struct implements provider interfaces that allow components like workqueue and leader election to emit metrics without direct dependencies on prometheus.\n\n### Grafana Architecture\n\n**Metric Definition (pkg/infra/metrics/metrics.go):**\nGrafana declares all metrics as package-level variables in a single metrics definition file:\n\n- **ExporterName constant**: Set to \"grafana\" as the namespace for metrics\n- **Metric Variables**: Declared directly (e.g., MInstanceStart, MPageStatus, MApiStatus, MProxyStatus, etc.) with types from prometheus client_golang\n- **init() function**: Uses `initMetricVars(reg prometheus.Registerer)` to register all metrics at startup\n- **Custom Initialization**: Some metrics use metricutil.NewCounterVecStartingAtZero() for custom initialization behavior\n\n**Service-Based Management (pkg/infra/metrics/service.go):**\nGrafana uses dependency injection via Wire for metrics management:\n\n- **ProvideService**: Returns InternalMetricsService that initializes metrics and handles graphite bridge\n- **ProvideRegisterer**: Returns `legacyregistry.Registerer()` (wrapping Kubernetes' legacyregistry)\n- **ProvideGatherer**: Returns a custom `multiRegistry` that combines multiple gatherers\n- **addPrefixWrapper**: Ensures all metrics get the \"grafana_\" prefix if not already present\n- **multiRegistry**: Combines Kubernetes gatherer (k8sGatherer) with prometheus.DefaultGatherer\n\n**Separate Instrumentation Server (pkg/server/instrumentation_service.go):**\nGrafana runs metrics exposition on a separate HTTP server:\n\n- **instrumentationService**: A service that runs independently with its own http.Server\n- **newInstrumentationServer()**: Creates an http.Server with `http.NewServeMux()` and handles `/metrics` using `promhttp.Handler()`\n- Runs on `:` + cfg.HTTPPort (configurable port)\n- Independent lifecycle management via BasicService interface\n\n**Wire Dependency Injection (pkg/infra/metrics/wireset.go):**\n- Uses Google Wire for dependency injection\n- Provides WireSet and WireSetForTest configurations\n- Integrates with broader application dependency graph in pkg/server/wire.go (line 397)\n\n### Key Differences\n\n**1. Registry Strategy:**\n- **Kubernetes**: Distributed metric registration across modules, centralized via legacyregistry\n- **Grafana**: Centralized metric definition in one file, distributed registration via initMetricVars()\n\n**2. HTTP Endpoint Exposure:**\n- **Kubernetes**: Metrics integrated into main API server routes via route installation classes\n- **Grafana**: Metrics exposed on separate dedicated HTTP server (separate port)\n\n**3. Metric Namespace:**\n- **Kubernetes**: Uses subsystem-based namespacing (apiserver_audit, apiserver_etcd, etc.)\n- **Grafana**: Adds \"grafana_\" prefix to all metrics via addPrefixWrapper\n\n**4. Multiple Gatherers:**\n- **Kubernetes**: Single defaultRegistry with explicit component registration\n- **Grafana**: Combines multiple gatherers (Kubernetes' legacyregistry + prometheus.DefaultGatherer) via multiRegistry pattern\n\n**5. Dependency Injection:**\n- **Kubernetes**: Manual initialization in init() functions, global registry access\n- **Grafana**: Wire-based dependency injection for service construction and configuration\n\n**6. Collector Integration:**\n- **Kubernetes**: Uses metrics provider pattern for pluggable collectors (workqueue, leader election)\n- **Grafana**: Uses service-based wrapper around Kubernetes metrics with graphite bridge integration\n\n### Common Elements\n\n1. Both use **prometheus/client_golang** library for metrics creation and exposition\n2. Both expose metrics on `/metrics` HTTP endpoint\n3. Both use **Counter, Gauge, Histogram, Summary** metric types from prometheus client\n4. Both support labeled metrics (CounterVec, HistogramVec, etc.)\n5. Both register metrics with a central registry that implements prometheus.Registerer interface\n6. Both use **promhttp** for HTTP exposition (promhttp.Handler() or promhttp.InstrumentMetricHandler())\n7. Both support gathering metrics with prometheus.Gatherer interface for exposition\n\n### Exposition Flow\n\n**Kubernetes:**\nComponent Code → legacyregistry.MustRegister(metric) → defaultRegistry → DefaultGatherer → Handler() → promhttp.HandlerFor() → HTTP /metrics endpoint\n\n**Grafana:**\nMetrics definition → initMetricVars(registerer) → register with prometheus → ProvideGatherer() → addPrefixWrapper + multiRegistry → instrumentationService → promhttp.Handler() → HTTP /metrics endpoint on separate server"
